Author: Reiner Herrmann <reiner@reiner-h.de>
Description: Use .object_arch to declare the architecture of the object file
 binutils >= 2.27.51.20161105-1 has stricter checking for this and no longer builds
 with .arch when newer .arch directives are used in the same file.
 See also: https://sourceware.org/ml/binutils/2006-09/msg00054.html
Bug: http://www.openwall.com/lists/musl/2017/01/04/6
Bug-Debian: https://bugs.debian.org/852214

--- a/src/thread/arm/atomics.s
+++ b/src/thread/arm/atomics.s
@@ -84,7 +84,7 @@
 	bx lr
 
 /* Tag this file with minimum ISA level so as not to affect linking. */
-.arch armv4t
+.object_arch armv4t
 .eabi_attribute 6,2
 
 .data
